        "text": "The document is an excerpt from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, specifically Appendix A, dated February 5, 2025. It defines several terms related to energy market operations:\n\n1. **Forecasted Movement**: Refers to changes in a resource's forecasted output between market intervals as per Section 44.3.\n\n2. **FPA**: Refers to Parts II and III of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. \u00a7 824 et seq., which may be amended over time.\n\n3. **Frequently Mitigated Unit**: A generating unit eligible for a Bid Adder under Section 39.8.\n\n4. **Full Capacity Deliverability Status**: Allows a generating facility to have a Net Qualifying Capacity up to its Qualifying Capacity, subject to CAISO's assessment.\n\n5. **Full Network Model (FNM)**: A computer-based model that includes the CAISO Balancing Authority Area's transmission network, modeling it as a looped network and interties in a radial fashion as per Section 27.5.\n\n6. **GADS**: Stands for Generating Availability Data System.\n\n7. **GDF**: Refers to Generation Distribution Factor.\n\n8. **General Reliability Network Upgrade (GRNU)**: Refers to reliability network upgrades that are not interconnection reliability network upgrades.\n\n9. **Generated Bid**: A post-market clean bid generated by CAISO using default energy and commitment cost bids, as per Section 40 or other applicable provisions, when a bid is not submitted by a Scheduling Coordinator.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Fifth_Replacement_FERC_Electric_Tariff/page_1247.jpg",
          "page_num": 1247,
          "title": "Fifth Replacement FERC Electric Tariff",
          "year": "",
          "market": "CAISO",
