        }
      },
      {
        "id": "7226a2af-3781-496a-8524-a484a660112d",
        "score": 0.50248414,
        "text": "The document is a section from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff. It outlines procedures related to market operations:\n\n1. **Virtual Award Information (6.5.8):** CAISO will post net cleared quantities of Virtual Awards for each trading day on OASIS by the close of the Real-Time Market.\n\n2. **Transmission Flowgate Constraint Information (6.5.9):** CAISO will post all transmission flowgate constraints with corresponding shadow prices on OASIS.\n\n3. **Protected Communications with Market Participants (6.5.10):** \n   - **Protected Data (6.5.10.1):** Data will be provided to parties with a Non-Disclosure Agreement.\n   - **Transmission Constraints Enforcement List (6.5.10.1.1):** After Day-Ahead Market results, CAISO will provide a list of enforced and non-enforced transmission constraints. This list is updated daily and provided before the next Day-Ahead Market. If not available daily, a monthly list will be provided.\n   - **Load Distribution Factors (6.5.10.1.2):** Three days post-trading day, CAISO will provide actual Load Distribution Factors for the Integrated Forward Market. This includes factors for each Default LAP's Pricing Nodes, especially where there is more than one customer. \n\nThe document is dated August 3, 2024, and is part of Section 6.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/CAISO/protocol/Fifth_Replacement_FERC_Electric_Tariff/page_117.jpg",
