      {
        "id": "6c3dfe3a-c2b1-4a91-95de-e5df24ccfa23",
        "score": 0.4935974,
        "text": "The document is a page from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, specifically Appendix F to the LGIA (Large Generator Interconnection Agreement). It outlines the addresses for delivery of notices and billings, which are currently unspecified and marked as \"[To be supplied]\" for the following entities:\n\n1. **Notices:**\n   - Participating TO (Transmission Owner)\n   - Interconnection Customer\n   - CAISO (California Independent System Operator)\n\n2. **Billings and Payments:**\n   - Participating TO\n   - Interconnection Customer\n   - CAISO\n\n3. **Alternative Forms of Delivery of Notices (telephone, facsimile, or e-mail):**\n   - Participating TO\n   - Interconnection Customer\n\nThe document is dated September 1, 2022, and labeled as Appendix Z.",
