      {
        "id": "069b7eaf-7fcc-4f38-99e2-b983f7464fec",
        "score": 0.4887268,
        "text": "The document is a section from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, specifically Appendix Y, dated August 3, 2024. It outlines various procedures and requirements related to interconnection studies and financial security for queue clusters.\n\nKey sections include:\n\n- **Deliverability Status**: Discusses confirmation, impact of modifications, commercial viability, and alignment with power purchase agreements.\n  \n- **Revisions to Final Interconnection Study Reports**: Covers handling substantial errors or omissions and adjustments to posting dates.\n\n- **Phase II Interconnection Study for Queue Clusters**: Details the scope, coordination with transmission planning, and financing of network upgrades.\n\n- **Additional Deliverability Assessment Options**: Includes options for full capacity deliverability and deliverability from non-participating transmission operators.\n\n- **Interconnection Financial Security**: Describes types, initial and additional postings, and effects of withdrawal or termination, including schedules for non-refundable portions.\n\nThis document is part of regulatory and procedural guidelines for managing interconnection and financial security in energy transmission.",
