      {
        "id": "c35b73f7-7862-4a43-a883-3a63ad0401be",
        "score": 0.4866215,
        "text": "The document is part of the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Tariff, specifically Appendix FF. It outlines two main sections:\n\n1. **Annual Reassessment Process (Section 12.13):** \n   - The CAISO will conduct an annual reassessment as per Section 7.4 of the GIDAP. This involves updating base case data before starting the GIDAP Phase II Interconnection Studies.\n   - The reassessment may lead to modifications in Delivery Network Upgrades and Off-Peak Network Upgrades, which are already identified in executed Generator Interconnection Agreements.\n   - These modifications are necessary to reflect current circumstances, including any changes in the queue of Interconnection Customers, withdrawals, and approved upgrades.\n   - Any changes affecting the scope, characteristics, or financial responsibility for these upgrades will be reflected through an amendment to the SGIA.\n\n2. **Notices (Article 13):**\n   - Details the procedure for delivering written notices, demands, or requests related to the agreement.\n   - Notices must be delivered in person, by recognized courier service, email, or first-class mail.\n   - Specific contact information sections are provided for the Interconnection Customer, Participating TO, and CAISO.\n\nThe document is dated December 17, 2024.",
