      "text": "TEL (503) 241-7242 ● jlb@dvclaw.com\nSuite 430\n107 SE Washington St.\nPortland, OR 97214\nApril 23, 2025\nVia Electronic Filing\nPublic Utility Commission of Oregon\nAttn: Filing Center\n201 High St. SE, Suite 100\nSalem OR 97301\nRe: In the Matter of Portland General Electric,\nInvestigation into Marginal Cost Study Treatment of Costs for Large Customers \nand Further Modifications to Portland General Electric Company's Rule C and \nRule I\nDocket No. UM 2377\nDear Filing Center:\nPlease find enclosed Google LLC’s Petition to Intervene in the above-referenced \ndocket. \nThank you for your assistance. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate \nto call.\nSincerely,\n/s/ Julitta Brannon\nJulitta Brannon\nParalegal\nEnclosure\nPAGE 1 – PETITION TO INTERVENE OF GOOGLE\nDAVISON VAN CLEVE, P.C.\n107 SE Washington St., Suite 430\nPortland, OR 97214\nTelephone (503) 241-7242\nBEFORE THE PUBLIC UTILITY COMMISSION\nOF OREGON\nUM 2377\nIn the Matter of \nPORTLAND GENERAL ELECTRIC \nCOMPANY,\nInvestigation into Marginal C",
      "highlights": [
        "Investigation into Marginal Cost Study Treatment of Costs for Large Customers and Further Modifications to Portland General Electric Company's Rule C and  ...   Pursuant to ORS § 756.525 and OAR § 860-001-0300(2), Google LLC (“Google”) hereby petitions the Oregon Public Utility Commission (“Commission”) to intervenein this proceeding with full party status as described in OAR § 860-001-0010(7). In support of 2. Google will be represented in this proceeding by Davison Van Cleve, P.C.(“DVC”). All documents relating to this proceeding should be served on Google’s representative as well as Google’s attorneys and DVC’s paralegal at the following addresses:3. Google is a limited liability company. Google, through its managed affiliates, owns and operates data centers in dozens of locations around the globe, includingOregon. As a data center owner and operator, Google’s business interests include potential development opportunities at new sites in Oregon and in the West, generally.4. On March 7, 2025, the Commission opened Docket No. UM 2377 to investigate marginal cost study treatment of costs for large customers and further modificationsto PGE’s Rule C and Rule I pursuant to the Commission’s Order No. 25-091 in Docket No. UE 430. Google’s interest in this proceeding relates to the policies that may be adopted and that mayimpact Google’s interests as a data center owner, including any possible expansion plans in Oregon. Because the outcome of this investigation will substantially and directly affect PGE’srates and programs and potentially create policy that could be more broadly applicable, Google requests leave to intervene in this Docket to represent its own interests.5. Google has reviewed the docket history as well as Staff’s Proposed Issues List filed on April 17, 2025. Google does not intend to raise any issues in addition to those6. Google also has experience participating in proceedings involving PGE’s rates and programs through its membership in the Data Center Coalition.in this proceeding will assist the Commission in resolving the issues in this proceeding and will not unreasonably broaden the issues, burden the record, or unreasonably delay this proceeding.7. As described above, Google has a direct and substantial interest in this proceeding that will not be adequately represented by any other party and may be affected by anyCommission determination made in connection with this proceeding. It is in the public interest WHEREFORE, Google respectfully requests that the Commission grant its"
