thority  ...   a) 100 kV Threshold for Regional Planning............................................................... 229 b) Independent Transmission System Planner............................................................ 232  ...   A. Identification of the action or inaction (18 C.F.R. § 385.206(b)(1)).............................. 244 B. Explanation of the Violation (18 C.F.R.§ 385.206(b)(2)).............................................. 246 C. Business, Commercial, Economic, or Other Issues Presented (18 C.F.R.  ...   D. Financial Impact (18 C.F.R. § 385.206(b)(4))................................................................ 248 E. Practical/Operational Impact (18 C.F.R.§ 385.206(b)(5))............................................. 250 F. Other Pending Proceedings (18 C.F.R. § 385.206(b)(6))................................................ 2501. CPUC Complaint Regarding Self-Planned Transmission Projects............................. 251 2. PJM: Replacement Process Senior Task Force and Consumer Challenges to Revised  ...   3. PJM: Consumers’ Objection To Secret Self-Planned Transmission........................... 257 4. PJM: Stakeholder Proposal re End-of-Life Projects................................................... 260  ...   G. Relief Requested (18 C.F.R. § 385.206(b)(7))................................................................ 271 H. Attachments (18 C.F.R.§ 385.206(b)(8))....................................................................... 271 I. Other Processes Resolve Complaint (18 C.F.R.§ 385.206(b)(9) & (10))...................... 272 J. Notice of Complaint (18 C.F.R. § 385.206(b)(10))........................................................ 273VIII. CONCLUSION............................................................................................................... 273Institute, Glass Packaging Institute, Public Citizen, ) Businesses Advocating for Tariff Equity, Carolina ) Utility Customers Association, Inc., Pennsylvania )Southwest Power Pool,"
