      "url": "https://epsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/EPSA-Co-Location-Conf-Comments-AD24-11-000.pdf",
      "title": "[PDF] EPSA Co-Location Conf. Comments AD24-11-000",
      "published_date": "2024-12-03T00:00:00.000Z",
      "text": "1\nUNITED STATES OF AMERICA\nBEFORE THE\nFEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSION\n)\nLarge Loads Co-Located at ) Docket No. AD24-11-000\nGenerating Facilities )\nTechnical Conference )\n)\nPOST-CONFERENCE COMMENTS OF \nTHE ELECTRIC POWER SUPPLY ASSOCIATION\nPursuant to the Commission’s November 28, 2024 Notice of Request for\nComments,\n1 the Electric Power Supply Association (“EPSA”)2 hereby submits these \ncomments on the Commission’s November 1, 2024 Commissioner-led Technical \nConference (“Technical Conference”) to discuss generic issues related to the co-location of \nlarge loads with generating facilities. As the conference discussion indicated, the novel \nconfigurations for co-location arrangements pose an array of scenarios that subsequently \nraise numerous questions regarding whether and how regulators can, should, or are \nrequired to address co-location rules, regulations, and procedures. As Commissioner Judy \nChang noted, this likely requires consideration of short-term approaches for the co-",
