      "text": "Butler Snow | Large Load Interconnection: Some Legal and Policy Issues[1]\n\nHome\n\nNews & Insights\n\nLarge Load Interconn ...\n\n# Large Load Interconnection: Some Legal and Policy Issues[1]\n\nFebruary 13, 2025 | by Bill A. Moore\n\nAttorney Publications\n\n## Large Load Interconnection: Some Legal and Policy Issues[1]\n\nFebruary 13, 2025\n\nBy Bill A. Moore\n\nClick here to download a PDF version of this article.\n\n## Introduction: The Challenge\n\nForecasts of growth in electricity consumption (“load”) across the United States are increasing remarkably. In just over the last few years, those forecasts have doubled and tripled.[2] Much of that growth is attributable to large loads, such as data centers, cryptocurrency mining operations, and other heavy-computing installations, which the President has declared vital to American national security and economic competitiveness.[3] Both large energy companies and load developers have made the same point, arguing that “interconnection of new large loads repr",
